# Slide Knowledge Locations

| What | Path |
|------|------|
| Raw source files (PPTX, immutable) | `knowledge/content/raw/` |
| Wiki (LLM-maintained markdown) | `knowledge/content/wiki/` |
| Wiki catalog | `knowledge/content/wiki/index.md` |
| Wiki timeline | `knowledge/content/wiki/log.md` |
| Wiki schema / conventions | `knowledge/content/SCHEMA.md` |
| Style / template (PPTX) | `knowledge/style/` |
| Output | `work/sessions/<YYYY-MM-DD-topic-slug>/slide-deck.pptx` |

## Non-negotiables

- All slide content must originate from PPTX files in `knowledge/content/raw/`. Do not invent facts.
- The wiki in `knowledge/content/wiki/` is the compiled content layer — the LLM writes and maintains it; humans read it.
- Raw PPTX files are immutable — the LLM reads them during ingest but never modifies them.
- A PPTX must be ingested (via the `ingest` skill) before its content appears in the wiki and can be used for slide generation.
- If content for a topic is missing from the wiki, tell the user — do not fill the gap.
- Output is always a `.pptx` file. No intermediate files.
